      "note_no": "171",
      "note": "This is a free rendering of the phrase \"the sacred month for the sacred month\", which is interpreted by all commentators in the sense given above. The \"sacred months\" during which, according to ancient Arab custom, all fighting was deemed utterly wrong, were the first, seventh, eleventh and twelfth months of the lunar calendar."
    },
    {
      "note_no": "172",
      "note": "Thus, although the believers are enjoined to fight back whenever they are attacked, the concluding words of the above verse make it clear that they must, when fighting, abstain from all atrocities, including the killing of non-combatants."
    }
